{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer to cover personal debts. While white-collar crimes of this nature require a penalty that serves as both a specific and general deterrent, the court must heavily weigh the mitigating factors present in this case. The defendant has no prior criminal record, indicating that this behavior is an isolated incident rather than a pattern of criminality. Furthermore, the defendant has already made efforts to partially repay the stolen funds, demonstrating remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. Balancing the need for accountability with the defendant's rehabilitation and the practical need for them to earn income to complete restitution, a relatively brief period of incarceration is appropriate.",
  "verdict": 6
}
